# Core Protocol

## Before you write code

1. Read `docs/Memory.md` — note **Active Phase**, blockers, last session.
2. Open **only** the doc slices you need (`Phases` / `Rules` / `Architecture` / `Design`). Open `PRD.md` only when product behavior is ambiguous.
3. If Memory and the user disagree → **ask**, then sync Memory. Do not code on a disputed phase.

## Authority (when docs conflict)

`PRD` → `Architecture` (Inabiya domains only; ignore LMS residue) → `Rules` → `Design` → `Phases` → `Memory`

## Hard locks (non-negotiable)

| Lock | Meaning |
|---|---|
| Stack | Next.js App Router · NestJS · Postgres+Prisma · Redis+BullMQ · Tailwind+shadcn · Zod · pnpm |
| No alternate stack | No Mongo, FastAPI/Django primary, CRA, Pages Router for new work, second ORM |
| Phase | Only active-phase P0/P1 unless human overrides **and** Memory logs it |
| Themes | Soft Gift (`gift`) ≠ Creator (`creator`) — never mix tokens |
| Domains | No LMS models (`Student`, `Hostel`, `Exam`, …) |

## Stop coding and escalate

Stack swap · cross-module Prisma · float money · auth/validation bypass · phase skip · theme mix · “temporary” security disable.

## Done means

Scope matches phase · Zod/DTO + AuthZ on mutations · migrations/env noted · non-trivial logic has one check · Memory session log updated.
